Standard and Poor's Corp said itassigned a preliminary AAA rating to 150 mln dlrs of 7-1/4 pctguaranteed subordinated bonds due 1992 of Nomura InternationalFinance PLC, the U.K. unit of Nomura Securities Co Ltd.    S and P cited the guarantee, which is a senior obligationof the parent company, the largest of the Big Four securitieshouses in Japan.    The rating agency noted that Nomura Securities has by farthe largest capital base in nominal terms of any securitiesfirm in the world and is conservatively leveraged. Reuter&#3;